<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8"?><!DOCTYPE topic  PUBLIC '-//OASIS//DTD DITA Topic//EN'  'topic.dtd'><topic id="GUID_DE1F55A2-4282-4F1A-AAE9-977E19B4EF64"><title>TCP AUX Retimer Topology</title><body><section id="SECTION_D178EB6B-FB96-49F8-B0AE-699ADF00A228"><fig id="FIG_tcp_aux_retimer_topology_diagram_1"><title>TCP AUX Retimer Topology Diagram</title><image href="FIG_tcp aux retimer topology diagram_1.png" scalefit="yes" id="IMG_tcp_aux_retimer_topology_diagram_1_png" /></fig><table id="TABLE_D178EB6B-FB96-49F8-B0AE-699ADF00A228_1"><title>TCP AUX Retimer Topology Notes</title><tgroup cols="2"><thead><row><entry>Note</entry><entry>Detail</entry></row></thead><tbody><row><entry><p>Number of vias allowed</p></entry><entry><p>No explicit limit, use best known routing practices.</p></entry></row><row><entry><p>Transmission line referencing</p></entry><entry><p>Reference planes can be continuous ground or continuous power that have low frequency peak to peak noise. Ground referencing is preferred.</p></entry></row><row><entry><p>ESD</p></entry><entry><p>Refer to USB4 ESD approved list in Barlowridge host router(BR HR) collateral.</p></entry></row><row><entry><p>AC cap value</p></entry><entry><p>Nominal 100 nF recommended (75 nF to 200 nF including tolerance).</p></entry></row><row><entry><p>Retimer</p></entry><entry><p>Applies to June Bridge topology. Consult re-timer datasheet for exact Aux channel implementation requirements.</p></entry></row><row><entry><p>Optional edge rate control</p></entry><entry><p>An edge rate reduction mechanism may be needed to comply with DisplayPort maximum Aux slew rate specification dependent on the retimer's Aux implementation.</p></entry></row><row><entry><p>Cs cap value</p></entry><entry><p>47 pF nominal.</p><p /></entry></row></tbody></tgroup></table></section><section id="SECTION_BE74CC82-492F-49E7-BA4D-7B9603BA2FBF"><title>Mainstream, Premium Mid Loss (PML), Tx</title><table id="TABLE_BE74CC82-492F-49E7-BA4D-7B9603BA2FBF_1"><ti